data.chText: （作为惩罚用棍子等）抽打，连续击打
data.enText: to hit a person or an animal many times with a stick, etc. as a punishment
to move or make sth move in a violent or uncontrolled way

data.chText: 有人在水里乱扑腾，显然遇到了危险。
data.enText: Someone was thrashing around in the water, obviously in trouble.

data.chText: 一条鲸鱼不住地用尾巴击水。
data.enText: A whale was thrashing the water with its tail.

data.chText: 她把头摇得像拨浪鼓似的。
data.enText: She thrashed her head from side to side.
to defeat sb very easily in a game

data.chText: 苏格兰队以5:1大胜英格兰队。
彻底讨论，反复讨论（以便作出决定）
data.enText: to discuss a situation or problem thoroughly in order to decide sth
a type of loud rock music
a party with music and dancing

means: (作为惩罚用棍子等)抽打，连续击打

data.chText: 彻底讨论，反复讨论（以便作出决定）
data.enText: to discuss a situation or problem thoroughly in order to decide sth

trans: 经反复讨论制订出（计划、协议）
讨论解决，商讨解决（问题、争端）

tr: a swimming kick used while treading water
beat thoroughly and conclusively in a competition or fight
example: We licked the other team on Sunday!

tr: beat the seeds out of a grain
move data into and out of core rather than performing useful computation
beat so fast that (the heart's) output starts dropping until (it) does not manage to pump out blood at all

example: The feverish patient thrashed around in his bed

value.def: If one player or team thrashes another in a game or contest, they defeat them easily or by a large score.

example.tran: 排名第二的流浪者队以 5: 0 大胜圣约翰斯通队。

value.tran: (在比赛、竞赛中)轻松击败，以大比分战胜

value.def: If you thrash someone, you hit them several times as a punishment.

example.ex: 'Liar!' Sarah screamed, as she thrashed the child. 'You stole it.'
example.tran: “叫你撒谎！”萨拉一边揍着孩子，一边尖叫道，“就是你偷的。”

value.tran: (作为惩罚)连续击打，接连殴打，痛打

value.def: If someone thrashes about, or thrashes their arms or legs about, they move in a wild or violent way, often hitting against something. You can also say that someone's arms or legs thrash about .

example.ex: Many of the crew died a terrible death as they thrashed about in shark-infested waters...
example.tran: 很多船员在鲨鱼成群的水域中拼命挣扎，死状惨不忍睹。

example.ex: ...dreams so vivid that I thrash inside my sleeping bag and cry out...
example.tran: 梦境太逼真了，我在睡袋里翻来滚去，喊出了声

example.ex: Jimmy collapsed on the floor, thrashing his legs about like an injured racehorse.
example.tran: 吉米瘫倒在地板上，像匹受伤的赛马一样拼命踢蹬着双腿。

value.tran: 猛烈摆动;翻来覆去;剧烈扭动(四肢)

value.def: If a person or thing thrashes something, or thrashes at something, they hit it continually in a violent or noisy way.

example.ex: ...a magnificent paddle-steamer on the mighty Mississippi, her huge wheel thrashing the muddy water...
example.tran: 广阔的密西西比河上行驶着一艘豪华庞大的明轮船，她巨大的轮子拍打着浑浊的河水

example.ex: Three shaggy-haired men thrash tunelessly at their guitars.
example.tran: 3 个头发蓬乱的男人没腔没调地乱弹着吉他。

example.ex: Harry always invited Charlie when he threw a thrash in his office.
example.tran: 哈里在办公室开派对时总不忘叫上查利。

trans: 经反复讨论制订出（计划、协议）
讨论解决，商讨解决（问题、争端）
